OL,3,CSchools should be phone-free zones,
OL,4,Ceducation secretary tells headteachers
OL,6,FThe education secretary has written to
OL,7,Fhead teachers in England, stressing
OL,8,Fthat schools should be phone-free
OL,9,Fthroughout the entire school day.
OL,11,FIn the letter, seen by ITV News,
OL,12,FBridget Phillipson writes that it is
OL,13,F"not appropriate for phones to be used
OL,14,Fas calculators, or for research" both
OL,15,Finside and outside of class time.
