OL,3,CSchools should be phone-free zones,
OL,4,Ceducation secretary tells headteachers
OL,6,FAccording to data supplied by the
OL,7,FDSIT, 99.9% of primary schools and 90%
OL,8,Fof secondary schools have mobile phone
OL,9,Fpolicies in place.
OL,11,FHowever, 58% of secondary school
OL,12,Fpupils reported mobile phones being
OL,13,Fused without permission in at least
OL,14,Fsome lessons, rising to 65% for key
OL,15,Fstage four pupils.
